g.text: Frittte clerk: "I mean, I didn't just see a middle-aged man try to steal a four re√°l raincoat, did I?"
Pain Threshold: She's like 14! You're humiliated in front of a minor, what's *wrong* with you, son?!
You: "I'm sorry... I'm such a mess lately..."
Interfacing: The packages are small. Discreet. Sloppily stacked, making them easier to take unnoticed -- no need to worry about knocking over a display.
Frittte clerk: "Yes -- buy it, please, don't steal it..." The clerk removes the garment from the dusty floor and hands it over.
Frittte clerk: "Here you go." The clerk removes the garment from the lower shelf and hands it over.
Interfacing: The sloppy stacking makes it more difficult to discern the missing one. You will be safe.
You: Try to grab a package. Any one of them. Slip it up your sleeve and...
Interfacing: Oh no! I said *don't* let it fall out with a thump! What did you do?
Knick-knacks Stand: To the left of some croissants and juice bottles, you see several packaged raincoats fill a low shelf. One is missing: the one you legally purchased.
Rhetoric: She says 'fuck with Frittte' like it's a saying, or like she's quoting someone. Maybe you can ask her about this later?
You: "No, you didn't. I didn't do it!"
Knick-knacks Stand: To the left of the croissants and juice bottles, several packaged raincoats fill a low shelf. One is missing. No one need be any wiser.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Really? A *plastic poncho*?" The lieutenant sighs and looks away.
Frittte clerk: The clerk stares at you, but doesn't say a thing for a moment or two.
Frittte clerk: "I mean, it doesn't even cost that much... like, why would you want to 'fuck with Frittte' over something like this?"
You: "Don't judge me. I needed it for an official police investigation."
Frittte clerk: "Fucking with Frittte is *dangerous*, you know." She scratches her cheek, thinking. "Just leave it there, I'll put it away later."
Knick-knacks Stand: To the left of the croissants and juice bottles, several packaged raincoats fill a low shelf. One, however, lies in the dusty floor: the one you tried and failed to steal.

Knick-knacks Stand: You see several packaged raincoats fill a low shelf beneath a display of croissants and juice bottles. The raincoats are transparent, except for the big 'FRITTTE' slogan on the back.
You: "I want to buy a raincoat."
Frittte clerk: "What is what?" The girl leans over the counter to see what you're referring to. "Uhm, it's a raincoat?"
Frittte clerk: "What is what?" The girl leans over the counter to see what you're referring to. "Uhm... a raincoat? You know -- like the one you tried to steal earlier?"
Frittte clerk: "What is what?" The girl leans over the counter to see what you're referring to. "Uhm... a raincoat? You know -- like the one you bought earlier?"
Interfacing: The girl delves into the magazine, hair covering her face... vision obscured, she cannot see your hand move.
Interfacing: The girl delves into the magazine, hair covering her face... vision obscured, she cannot see your hand move.
Knick-knacks Stand: To the left of the croissants and juice bottles, several packaged raincoats fill a low shelf. One is missing: the one you tried to steal, but then legally purchased.
Interfacing: Down onto one knee. Pretending to do up a shoelace. Take a loose package from the bottom. Slip it in the old sleeve. The girl doesn't notice *a thing*.
Volition: Look at it, detective. And be ashamed. Until you make it right by *legally purchasing* that raincoat, I'll make sure you feel guilty every time you see it.
Frittte clerk: "If you want to buy one then it's only four re√°l." She taps on the glass counter. The raincoats patiently await purchase.
Interfacing: Her attention is drawn to the raincoats. Stealing one undetected will now be more difficult.
Volition: A wrong has been made right. You may rest easy now.
Endurance: This will keep you nice and warm out there. Good choice, if a bit goofy looking...
Frittte clerk: "Um, did you..." The girl stares at the package lying on the floor. It looks a little sad as it lies in the dusty floor.
